FL Jump analysis

Detection

Same setup. We count the total number of jumps detected divided by number of jumps estimated (across 5000 distinct data vectors of \(n=200\) for the middle-jump case). The black line is binary segmentation, green line is fused lasso. The left is for 2-step algorithm, while the right is for 3-step algorithm.

Number of jumps detected in the correct vincity

For delta = 2 or delta = 4, we also count the number of jumps in the correct vincity.
